The GUIEnvironment support module simplifies some handling methods:


  @{" Screen support " LINK GES-Screen}

  @{" Gadget support " LINK GES-Gadget}

  @{" Font support " LINK GES-Font}

@ENDNODE

@NODE GES-Screen "Screen Support"

GUIEnvSupport exports some predefined display IDs:

  GES_HiresPalID, GES_HiresID, GES_LoresPalID, GES_LoresID.

Using this instead of the ones defined in graphics, often makes importing
graphics needless.

@ENDNODE

@NODE GES-Gadget "Gadget Support"

GUIEnvSupport offers the GADDESC and the GADOBJS makros which calculate
the tag value for the belonging gadget description tags !

The GEHUpdateEntryGadgetAHook function is a callback hook which can be used
for gadtools entry text gadgets (STRING_KIND, INTEGER_KIND). If you
set the up function to this hook (using the GEG_UpAHook tag), everytime a
IDCMP_GADGETUP message for this gadget arrives, the belonging variable will
get the new value of the gadget !
(But only of course if notification was set for this gadget !)

@ENDNODE

@NODE GES-Font "Font Support"

The TopazAttr() function returns a pointer to an initialized TextAttr
structure for the topaz 8 font !

@ENDNODE


